programme.title: Martial Arts History Museum-Cynthia Rothrock
programme.desc: Officially named, “Queen of the Martial Arts,” Cynthia Rothrock is considered one of the most historic figures in martial arts history. or five consecutive years, she was the undefeated World Champion in the karate tournament circuit. She has graced the cover of over 60 martial arts magazines and was inducted into the prestigious Martial Arts History Museum’s Hall of Fame at its inception in 1999. In the 1980s, she became one of the biggest box office draws in both Hong Kong and America for her action films. To date, she has starred in over 60 films and was also named “Queen of the Martial Arts in Films”. She continues to be one of the greatest advocates for the martial arts conducting countless seminars throughout the world.

programme.title: Martial Arts History Museum-Gerald Okamura
programme.desc: Officially called the "scariest man alive" by Black Belt magazine, we go behind the scenes of one of the most awesome Asian bad guys, Gerald Okamura. From his iconic role at the Hatchett Man in "Big Trouble in Little China," to his many appearances as an evil bad dude, we explore Gerald Okamura's history, his life and his legendary career as one of the top weapons experts in America. Gerald Okamura was inducted into the Martial Arts History Museum's Hall of Fame in 2003. Directed by William Ford with Director of Photography Jim Towns.

programme.title: Shaolin Heroes
programme.desc: During the declining years of Ming dynasty, Mongolians sent secret agents to intrude central China and tried to obtain "The Light Sword" a mighty sword, which can gather all brave wanderers. The son of Lung Chen Ying master of the Light Sword style learns of the plot and kills the leader of secret mission and temporarily stopped the Mongolian's ambition.

programme.title: Flash Legs
programme.desc: A band of thieves, known as the Eight Dragons, commit murder in the process of a stealing a treasure map. They decide three years is long enough for the heat to die down and allow them to search for their hidden fortune. But none of the thieves trusts any of his brothers-in-crime to keep the map that long. Their leader's solution is to cut the map into eight pieces, one for each bandit. Meanwhile, a pair of relentless lawmen is after them. One policeman is killed in their battle with the first bandit they find. The remaining cop, Fong Yee, is all the more determined to hunt down the other seven. One by one, he collects the pieces of the map as his flashy, flashing feet kick his opponents into submission or death.

programme.title: Tarzan's Revenge (1938)
programme.desc: In his only turn as Tarzan, 1936 Olympic decathlon champion Glenn Morris cavorts in the jungle with another Olympian, swimming star Eleanor Holm. Neither athlete pursued a movie career, so this film is a rarity in that we see them together! Also of note to film buffs is the musical score by Oscar nominated Hugo Riesenfeld (Make a Wish), one of the top composers of Hollywood's early sound era. Riesenfeld worked with such giants of the cinema as Cecil B. DeMille, D.W. Griffith, and F.W. Murnau.

programme.title: American Empire (1942)
programme.desc: This epic of America's westward march stars Leo Carrillo and Preston Foster in a tale of men building a cattle empire, only to battle rustlers, the weather, and each other! The romantic adventure from director William C. McGann (In Old California, Alcatraz Island) features a strong leading performance by Oscar nominated RKO star Richard Dix (Cimarron, The Ghost Ship) plus cinematography by six-time Oscar nominee Russell Harlan (To Kill a Mockingbird, Rio Bravo).

programme.title: The Mark of the Hawk (1957)
programme.desc: Eartha Kitt and Sidney Poitier star in this tale of a man named Obam (Poitier) and his struggles in British occupied Africa. As tension divides the country, Obam seeks racial harmony through peace. He enlists the help of his wise wife (Kitt) and a sympathetic missionary (John McIntire), but his fight to make a difference in an atmosphere of African nationalism is tougher than he thinks. Can he make changes to what appears to be a doomed situation?

programme.title: The Perils of Pauline (1947)
programme.desc: Featuring Frank Loesser’s Oscar nominated song, "I Wish I Didn’t Love You So," The Perils of Pauline is about the rise to fame of silent screen star Pearl White (Betty Hutton). Directed by George Marshall (The Blue Dahlia, Houdini), the cast includes such stars as Billy De Wolfe, John Lund, and William Demarest, plus appearances by silent screen aces Snub Pollard and Chester Conklin. Still, it’s Hutton’s movie all the way – her energy and charisma highlight this tribute to the golden age of moviemaking!

programme.title: Journey to the Center of Time
programme.desc: A team of scientific researchers travel into the far future and distant past.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders
programme.desc: A newspaper editor decides to send his girlfriend, who is also a reporter on the paper, undercover to try out for the cheerleading team for the Dallas Cowboys in order to do an "insider's" story.

programme.title: All American Co-ed (1941)
programme.desc: When all-girl school Mar Brynn slanders Quinceton College as a publicity stunt, the boys' school promptly sends Bob Sheppard (Johnny Downs) to Mar Brynn dressed as a girl. Bob infiltrates the campus, but falls in love with Virginia (Frances Landford), a sweetheart who only wishes to put on the school show. Can Bob restore the dignity of Quinceton and still keep the girl? The movie's cast includes Alan Hale Jr. ("Gilligan's Island"), silent screen star Harry Langdon, and an uncredited Mary Windsor as "The Carrot Queen". Edward Ward's score was nominated for an Academy Award, as was the song "Out of the Silence."

programme.title: Battle of the Worlds
programme.desc: A runaway asteroid dubbed "The Outsider" mysteriously begins orbiting the Earth and threatens it with lethal flying saucers.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Creeping Terror
programme.desc: In this episode of Mystery Science Theater 3000, Joel and his space traveling crew watch "The Creeping Terror."

programme.title: Indestructible Man (1956)
programme.desc: This is the movie you saw as a kid but can’t remember the title! Lon Chaney Jr. stars as “Butcher” Benton, a con who goes to his execution vowing to kill his former partners in crime. When his corpse is inadvertently brought back to life during a scientific experiment, he makes good on his deadly promises! This oddball feature was directed by Jack Pollexfen, a former newspaperman turned screenwriter, whose credits include Daughter of Dr. Jekyll, and The Man From Planet X...

programme.title: The Wasp Woman
programme.desc: A cosmetics queen develops a youth formula from jelly taken from queen wasps. She fails to anticipate the typical hoary side-effects. (BW)

programme.title: Bermuda Triangle
programme.desc: The passengers and crew of a boat on a summer cruise in the Caribbean stray near the famed Bermuda Triangle, and mysterious things start happening.

programme.title: Bluebeard (1945)
programme.desc: It’s the tale of the infamous serial killer of Paris, Bluebeard! Cult director Edgar G. Ulmer is behind this film that follows the story of puppeteer and portrait artist, Gaston Morrell (John Carradine). Also starring Jean Parker and Nils Asther, this Poverty Row drama is still loaded with macabre thrills!

programme.title: Beast from the Haunted Cave
programme.desc: A giant spider stalks a band of thieves in this schlocky thriller from Gene Corman Productions. The story follows gangster Alexander Ward and his crew as they enlist the help of a local ski-instructor in the heist of several gold bars. But when they use explosives to create a distraction, they disturb the lair of a massive spider! Monte Hellman, the man behind such cult favorites as Two-Lane Blacktop, made his directorial debut with Beast From Haunted Cave. Trivia note: This movie debuted on a double bill with The Wasp Woman.

programme.title: Come on Cowboys (1924)
programme.desc: The Mesquiteers are back! This time they're helping out a friend who has been framed for counterfeiting. And one of their pledges is to look after his young daughter. Robert Livingstone, Ray Corrigan, and Max Terhune star in this Republic Pictures feature, bringing all the usual laughs and action you know from the other Mesquiteer films!

programme.title: Second Chorus (1940)
programme.desc: Fred Astaire (Funny Face, Swing Time) and Burgess Meredith (Of Mice and Men, Rocky) star as a couple of trumpet players trying to make their way into Artie Shaw’s band. Shaw received two Oscar nominations for his work on the film, one for Best Music Score, and one for the song, ‘Love of my Life’, which he co-wrote with Johnny Mercer. The rest of the cast includes Paulette Goddard (Modern Times, The Great Dictator) as the band manager, and Charles Butterworth (Love Me Tonight), with direction by H.C. Potter (Mr. Blandings Builds his Dream House).

programme.title: The Ghost Town Mystery
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: Battle in the Clouds
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: The Stratosphere Adventure
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: The Gold Ship
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: Harbor Pursuit
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: Till the Clouds Roll By
programme.desc: An all-star cast fills out this energetic biopic of Broadway pioneer Jerome Kern (Robert Walker). Featuring tunes from the Kern songbook ("Ol Man River," "Smoke Gets in Your Eyes," and more than 20 others), the movie includes such performers as June Allyson, Judy Garland, Van Heflin, Lena Horne, Cyd Charisse, Van Johnson, Angela Lansbury, Kathryn Grayson, Lucille Bremer, Dinah Shore, and the Chairman of the Board himself, Frank Sinatra!

programme.title: The Garden of Eden
programme.desc: A FASCINATING FOLDEROL OF FUN! One of the definitive classics of the American silent film era, The Garden of Eden is a decadent, sumptuous romance adapted from Avery Hopwood's stage production, featuring a typically magnetic performance from silent film siren Corrine Griffith (The Divine Lady) as beautiful Viennese signer Toni Le Brun. When her mysterious benefactor, posing as a wardrobe mistress, turns out to be a wealthy baroness in disguise, Toni must face the unappealing reality that her new lover, and soon to be husband, may be more interested in her inevitable fortune than in winning her heart. This uplifting epic was capably helmed by two-time Oscar winning director Lewis Milestone (All Quiet on the Western Front, Mutiny on the Bounty), working from a complex and masterful screenplay from Oscar winning scribe Hanns Kraly.

programme.title: Arizona Thunderbolt
programme.desc: When Sue Bixby becomes his new boss, stagecoach robber Talbot reforms and goes after her rustled cattle. When he and his men are outnumbered fighting Lloyd's gang, Randall rides to get circus man Mahoney and his man shooting cannon.

programme.title: Breakfast in Hollywood (1946)
programme.desc: A fun cast headlines this feature about radio’s greatest daytime program! Bonita Granville, Beulah Bondi, Billie Burke, and Zasu Pitts are here as audience members who have come to enjoy a popular radio show (hosted by Tom Breneman). Meanwhile Hedda Hopper, Spike Jones, and Nat ‘King’ Cole appear as themselves. Nat sings ‘It’s Better To Be By Yourself,’ while other tunes are performed by Andy Russell, and Spike Jones and His City Slickers!

programme.title: The Big Wheel (1949)
programme.desc: An ambitious car mechanic (Mickey Rooney), determined to follow in his father’s footsteps, battles his way up the circuit to become an auto racing champion. But a fatal mistake on the track threatens to change everything for the cocky young driver, who’s set his sights on the Indianapolis 500. The exciting story unfolds against a backdrop of adrenaline-fueled racing action, and co-stars Thomas Mitchell and Hattie McDaniel.

programme.title: Carnival Story
programme.desc: An American carnival in Germany sets the scene for sin, sex and melodrama.

programme.title: Lying Lips (1939)
programme.desc: A nightclub singer (Edna Mae Harris) is framed for murder and sent to prison in this drama from writer/director Oscar Micheaux. Known for his complex approach to films about race relations, Micheaux’s cast includes Robert Earl Jones as the detective trying to prove the singer’s innocence. Among the featured musical numbers are ‘You Must Have Been a Beautiful Baby’, and ‘Chinatown My Chinatown’.

programme.title: House On Haunted Hill
programme.desc: A millionaire offers ten thousand dollars to five people if they agree to stay overnight in a large, spooky, rented house. When you consider that the millionaire is Vincent Price, and the film is directed by schlock master William Castle, you can bet the five guests are in for a long, bumpy night. This "super shocker of the century" was a smash hit upon its 1959 release. For architecture buffs, the home used for the exteriors of the haunted house was actually designed by Frank Lloyd Wright and built in 1924!

programme.title: The Little Princess (1939)
programme.desc: Shirley Temple was near the end of her reign as Hollywood’s top child star when she starred in Darryl F. Zanuck’s production of "The Little Princess." She plays Sara Crewe, the privileged daughter of Captain Reginald Crewe. When the Captain leaves to fight in Africa’s Boer War, Sara is enrolled into an upper-crust school for girls in London. All is well until Sara’s father is reported dead. When Sara’s intuition tells her the Captain is still alive, she begins hunting London military hospitals, culminating in what "Times’s" critic Janet Maslin called “...a happy ending sure to make even grown-up viewers cry.”

programme.title: Bowery at Midnight
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi is a college professor by day and runs a soup kitchen and hospital by night in New York City's Bowery section - but it's just a front for more sinister activities. When things get out of hand, Lugosi kills his henchmen, who wind up as zombies in the cellar. Director Wallace Fox, who had already worked with Lugosi on two previous Monogram films, Spooks Run Wild and The Corpse Vanishes, comes through with a true horror gem.

programme.title: Attack From Space
programme.desc: Benevolent aliens from the planet Emerald send superhero Starman to protect Earth from invasion by an evil alien race called the Spherions. When Starman arrives on Earth, he discovers a conspiracy involving Earth's top scientists, and he must root out the traitors and also stop the impending alien invasion.

programme.title: Killers from Space
programme.desc: After suffering a traumatic plane crash, an atomic scientist named Doug Martin is convinced he has been abducted by Aliens.

programme.title: The Ape
programme.desc: Kindly Dr. Adrian (Boris Karloff) is on the verge of creating a polio serum. Unfortunately, in order to complete his experiment he needs spinal fluid from a recently deceased human. All seems hopeless, but when a wild ape escapes from a nearby circus, Dr. Adrian's research takes on a ghastly new dimension. Director William Nigh (Black Dragons, Desert Nights) helmed this Poverty Row thriller from a screenplay co­written by Hollywood legend Curt Siodmak (The Wolfman, I Walked With A Zombie). Who will you root for – the jungle beast, or the man of science?

programme.title: Monster Maker
programme.desc: From Hollywood’s Poverty Row comes this sordid tale of a mad scientist turning his enemies into hideously deformed creatures. J. Carrol Naish (House of Frankenstein) stars as Dr. Igor Markoff, the amoral genius who uses a dangerous virus to create monsters! Also starring Ralph Morgan, Glenn Strange, Tala Birell, Ace the Wonderdog, and as always, Ray Corrigan appears as the gorilla.

programme.title: Right Hand (1956)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Hands (1953)
programme.desc: Friday and Smith are assigned to investigate the strangulation of an unidentified woman in a hotel room. With no leads and no clues, and no idea of who she is, they must start from scratch to find her killer.

programme.title: The Inheritance (1959)
programme.desc: A series of women pass away shortly after wearing a necklace given to them by Michael Barry, a washed up drunk who has become superstitious following the shocking events.

programme.title: The Positive Negative (1959)
programme.desc: After a nightclub photographer is threatened by gangsters who want the negative of a picture she took of a wealthy man, she reaches out to Mike for help.

programme.title: Day of Reckoning
programme.desc: Ben Cartwright gives a strip of fertile farming land to an Indian who had previously saved Ben’s life. Things take a deadly turn, however, when the land ends up being next to a very racist farmer.

programme.title: Duke Becomes a Father
programme.desc: Mlle. Denise comes back for the birth of her dog's puppies as well as to see Jed. "Courtin' and sparkin'" ensues.

programme.title: The Case of the Haunted Gainsborough (1955)
programme.desc: Malcolm MacGregan is at risk of losing his family’s Scottish castle if he can’t make the mortgage payment by midnight.

programme.title: General Practitioner
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Big Greeny Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Celia's Pen Pal
programme.desc: A clerk named Stanley finds himself embroiled in the chaotic ongoings of New York City tourists inside an upscale hotel.

programme.title: Lesson in Citizenship
programme.desc: After Jim Anderson scolds the children for their indolence towards good deeds, they get carried away with acts of charity.

programme.title: Lights of Old Santa Fe
programme.desc: Roy Rogers gets involved when his buddy finds himself at odds with a rival rodeo operator. There's plenty of singing in this musical western, plus enough action to make you realize that Roy Rogers was much more than a singing cowboy! With a cast that includes Dale Evans, George 'Gabby' Hayes, Lloyd Corrigan, and Tom Keene, director Frank McDonald gives us a fun thrill ride through old Santa Fe. Trigger is here, too!

programme.title: Flying Wild
programme.desc: The East Side Kids are at it again! The fifth installment of the beloved East Side Kids franchise from Monogram Pictures Corporation is another laugh-a-minute slapstick adventure that checks in with gang members Skinny, Danny Graham, Peewee, Algy Reynolds, and Scruno as they work at the Reynolds Aviation Company. Hilarity ensures when our gang suspects a doctor, who runs an air ambulance service, is secretly a spy transporting secret information from the plant to enemy agents.

programme.title: The Jungle Book (1942)
programme.desc: There couldn't have been a better way to showcase Rudyard Kipling's famous jungle tale than in eye-popping Technicolor under the fantastical direction of Zoltan Korda ("Sahara"), and filling the role of Mowgli with the legendary Sabu ("Elephant Boy," "The Thief of Bagdad"). This 1942 feature was nominated for four Academy Awards (including one for Miklós Rózsa's musical score) and serves as a nice companion piece to the beloved 1967 Disney cartoon. But beware; there are no singing animals here, just a darker, more realistic depiction of the jungle striking back at those who would violate its secret code!

programme.title: A Night in Casablanca
programme.desc: In post-war Casablanca, Ronald Kornblow (Groucho Marx) takes on the role of a hotel manager, unaware that no one else will dare take the position! The hotel has been the hiding spot of treasures by war criminals, and their only means to access it undetected is by murdering the hotel managers.

programme.title: The Milky Way (1936)
programme.desc: This was Harold Lloyd’s most highly regarded talkie, and also one of the last films he would appear in. He plays Burleigh Sullivan, a timid milkman who finds himself in the seedy world of prizefighting. Though he thinks his success is based on his ability to duck, it’s actually because his manager is bribing his opponents to fall down! Adolphe Menjou and Lionel Stander also star in this little classic (dubbed “uproariously funny” by Time magazine). It’s from director Leo McCarey, a triple Oscar winner who gave us such great films as Duck Soup and Going My Way.

programme.title: Dishonored Lady (1947)
programme.desc: Unbridled passion…scandal…murder! This seductive crime drama slickly directed by Oscar nominee Robert Stevenson (“Mary Poppins”) stars classic beauty Hedy Lamarr as Madeleine Damien, the fashion editor of an upscale Manhattan magazine in the midst of a breakdown. Considered wildly controversial for its time, even after the Hays Office demanded large-scale omissions of what it considered to be gratuitous sex and violence, “Dishonored Lady” nonetheless represents yet another complex and daring performance from the matchless Lamarr.

programme.title: Ten Little Indians
programme.desc: Nina Foch and Barry Jones star in this adaptation of Agatha Christie's mystery following ten suspects who are killed off one by one inside an isolated island mansion.

programme.title: Mesa of Lost Women
programme.desc: Spider-women lure men to their death in this thriller from the golden era of Drive-in schlock! This story of a mad scientist (Jackie Coogan) is regarded as one of the worst movies ever made. Still, dig the crazy guitar and piano score which was purloined by Ed Wood Jr. for Jail Bait, and notice a couple of Wood regulars (Dolores Fuller and Lyle Talbot) in the credits. What you have here is a sort of cousin to the films of Ed Wood, but one that can stand on its own as being truly awful. Enjoy!

programme.title: Great News
programme.desc: From the uncrowned king of industrial and educational training films, Jam Handy, comes this vintage 1950s short.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 5
programme.desc: Guest starring Imogene Coca and Lainie Kazan along with a variety og skits including a `V.I.P' sketch about Miss America, Carol, Harvey and guest Imogene Coca perform a coffee commercial sketch, guest Lainie Kazan performs a `Sunnyside'/`Silver Lining' medley, and duets with Carol on `Watch What Happens', Carol and Harvey as `Bonnie and Clod', a `Little Pianos' production number with the cast and dancers and the Charwoman does a striptease pantomime and sings `There's No Business Like Show Business'.

programme.title: Season 16 Episode 107
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: House of the Black Death
programme.desc: Two brothers, both of whom are warlocks, use their powers and covens of witches to battle over the family fortune.

programme.title: Devil's Partner
programme.desc: An old man sells his soul to the devil, and turns into a young man. He then uses witchcraft and black magic to win a woman from his rival.

programme.title: Chained for Life
programme.desc: This “bold, daring and frank” exploitation film features famed conjoined twins, the vaudeville sensations Violet and Daisy Hilton, portraying fictionalized versions of themselves in a narrative that reflects their tragic and unfortunate lives. Used and mistreated by their craven manager, the Siamese twins find themselves in trouble with the law when one of them murders a duplicitous scamp after he jilts her sister following a devastating sham marriage. Equal parts compelling and heartbreaking, Chained for Life doubles as both a thrilling noir and a sad account of the ill-fated Hilton Sisters.

programme.desc: A stranger-than-fiction tale about amputee John Wood who accidentally sold off his mummified limb and his quest to regain custody of his body part from the person that paid to acquire it. But beyond the surface of this tabloid fodder is a story of addicti

programme.desc: Academy Award-winning filmmaker Daniel Junge and producer Johnny Knoxville examine the life, career, and legacy of Evel Knievel, the man from Montana who stared death in the face to become a legendary daredevil and heroic icon.

programme.title: Bluefin
programme.desc: Endangered giant bluefin tuna have returned to Prince Edward Island in surprising abundance after a complete disappearance from overfishing. But something strange is going on. Tuna no longer fear humans. A tale of epic stakes about an extraordinary specie

programme.title: Entrapped
programme.desc: The FBI claimed it exposed a dangerous group of men in a massive entrapment operation over an alleged plot to attack a U.S. Army base in New Jersey. But were they really terrorists?

programme.title: The Thousand Year Journey
programme.desc: "Routine is the enemy of time." Jedidiah Jenkins rides his bicycle from Oregon to Patagonia, the southern tip of South America, while expounding upon ideas that made him leave a job he loved for the open road.

programme.desc: As Chinese filmmaker Nanfu Wang travels across America, she encounters Dylan. Fascinated, Nanfu follows Dylan with her camera on a journey that spans years.

programme.title: In The Shadow Of The Hill
programme.desc: The residents of Rio de Janeiro's largest slum seek justice for a local man they believe has been murdered by the police.

programme.desc: A documentary-horror film exploring the phenomenon of 'Sleep Paralysis' through the eyes of eight very different people who find themselves trapped between the sleeping and waking worlds.

programme.title: The S Word
programme.desc: A suicide attempt survivor is on a mission to find fellow survivors and document their stories of courage, insight and humor. Along the way, she discovers a rising national movement transforming personal struggles into action.

programme.title: Holy Rollers: The True Story of Card Counting Christians
programme.desc: Holy Rollers follows the rise of arguably the largest and most well-funded blackjack team in America-made up entirely of churchgoing Christians.

programme.desc: In this real-life "My Big Fat Greek Wedding,” an Indian-American man gets help from his parents and extended family so he can start looking for a wife the traditional Indian way.

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai‘i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho‘onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

This black comedy shines a glaring light on Randy (Hara) & Ralph (Stuart), a longtime gay couple who cannot stand each other... but can’t afford to get divorced.

programme.desc: A pre-Madonna primer that raises questions about race, sex and subcultural style, Voguing: The Message traces the roots of this gay Black and Latino dance form, which appropriates and plays with poses and images from mainstream fashion.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.title: Engaged
programme.desc: ENGAGED is a short romantic comedy that follows Darren (Daniel K. Isaac), who keeps trying – and failing – to propose to his boyfriend Elliot (Ryan Jamaal Swain). When their relationship is put into an uncomfortable spotlight during a friend’s outrageous engagement party, Darren realizes he actually might be self–sabotaging himself due to unresolved insecurities about his sexuality.

programme.title: Dating My Mother
programme.desc: Unemployed and living in his New Jersey hometown, brash screenwriter Danny spends his days practicing yoga, sipping red wine, and power-walking with his mother Joan. But when she reveals she’s seeing another man, their version of domestic bliss comes crashing down. DATING MY MOTHER follows the intimate and tumultuous relationship between a single mother and her gay son as they navigate the dizzying world of online dating. While they search for their versions of Mr. Right, mother and son discover that sometimes you need to be apart in order to grow together.

programme.title: The QueerX Awards
programme.desc: The circus is in town and just in time for National Coming Out Day! Welcome to the 2021 QueerX Awards brought to you by Lexus. Join us as hosts, Drew Droege and Raneir Pollard, take us on a carnival tour of LGBTQ music, films, and icons! Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. And don’t miss the special performances by Chanel and the Circus, Mila Jam, and Alsace Carcione.

programme.title: Davis Mallory | Heavy
programme.desc: The music video for "Heavy" by Davis Mallory featuring Blake Lieder and Daisha McBride. The music video for "Lifeline" by Davis Mallory featuring Allouche. The music video for "Little Victory" by Davis Mallory. A Look behind the scenes at Miami Pride 2021 with Davis Mallory

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S2 E1 | While On is working on his new MO underwear collection and traveling to Los Angeles to do press for his show, his fiancé struggles to navigate a broken justice system in an effort to find out more details about the end of his parole program since On’s dreams of a perfect wedding depend on it.

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S2 E2 | On meets with his perfume factory before traveling to Tel Aviv for a photoshoot and clothing line collaboration. Meanwhile, we get to know a bit more about his fiancée and his connection to personal training. On is encouraging Dave to open his own gym and dream big.

programme.title: For The Love Of Food
programme.desc: In this poignant and culturally reflective documentary, meet the movers and shakers behind the young and erupting food media industry.

programme.title: BIFL
programme.desc: Expectations, different shades of intimacy, & what it really means to love someone.

programme.title: For Izzy
programme.desc: The lives of a recovering queer addict and her single mother change forever when they move in next door to a widowed father and his adult daughter with autism.

programme.title: Ian Harvie: May The Best C--k Win
programme.desc: Ian Harvie is not quite the kind of man you might think. He's redefining what it means to be a dude through a fresh perspective on sex/sexuality with some seriously funny and new kinds of dick jokes. Unafraid to quip about subjects no other comedian has ever touched, Ian’s performance challenges the traditionally macho, sex-obsessed world of stand up in ways you won’t believe, proving that laughter cuts across all identities and ultimately unites us all in MAY THE BEST C--K WIN. Oh and, Ian is the world's first trans man comedian with a stand up comedy special.

programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight – filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

programme.title: Unlikely Family
programme.desc: Follow this Unlikely Family as it challenges the archaic ideology that being openly gay - and Christian - is incompatible.

programme.title: Amplify Voices
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Professional athletes and fitness experts come together to share their experiences being LGBTQ+ in sports. Discussing how things have changed over the years and the importance of bringing more inclusion to athletics.

programme.title: El Canto Del Colibri
programme.desc: Much like the seldom-heard song of the hummingbird, the voices of Latino fathers are rarely heard addressing LGBTQ issues. These voices are amplified in a groundbreaking documentary - the first of its kind.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S3 E3 | In this episode of The Q Agenda, we have an in-depth conversation about Black Lives Matter, transphobia, and police brutality with guest host Carolina Gutierrez. Plus, actor and activist Omar Sharif Jr. shares his experience coming out in Egypt underneath the spotlight.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S3 E4 | In this episode of The Q Agenda, we sit down with renowned publicist Howard Bragman to discuss his upbringing and the upcoming election. Writer-director duo Leita Solomon and Wes Akuobi talk about their controversial film, "The Cypher." Plus, we discuss the departure of Vanderpump Rules cast members after racist comments.

programme.title: Drag Kids
programme.desc: Drag has always been about breaking down barriers and daring to do the unexpected. Now, a new type of queen is on the scene: she’s fierce, she’s living in a time of unprecedented access to queer culture, and she’s younger than ever before. She’s a drag kid and she’s a long way from the era of the queens who led the Stonewall Riots nearly 50 years ago. Stephan, Jason, Bracken and Nemis have never met, but they’re united by a shared passion for drag. They are about to come together for the first time – to perform Lady Gaga’s ‘Born This Way’ at the world-famous Montreal Pride Festival. As they prepare for the big show, each faces their own unique challenges, as well as challenges they have in common - deep feelings of isolation and the struggle of trying to claim a place of your own on the fringes of a fringe culture. Drag Kids is a beautiful, daring, and touching portrait of four kids chasing freedom and friendship through the art of drag.

programme.title: Coming of Age in Cherry Grove
programme.desc: Founded in 1869, Cherry Grove (Fire Island, NY) is considered by most to be the first openly LGBTQ community in the United States. It has become known as one of the most accepting resort communities in the world – a place where you can not only discover who you are, but also freely experiment with who or what (gender) you may want to become. Cherry Grove is also known for the famous “INVASION” – an annual ritual that takes place every July 4th as a celebration of gender acceptance. This film tells the stories of a variety of long-term residents and what they find so wonderful about life in Cherry Grove.

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai‘i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho‘onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S1 | A Revry Original Reality Series, ‘Putting On’ follows a young entrepreneur, On Mekahel, as he struggles to launch his underwear line with his ex-boyfriend.

programme.title: Voguing The Message
programme.desc: A pre-Madonna primer that raises questions about race, sex and subcultural style, Voguing: The Message traces the roots of this gay Black and Latino dance form, which appropriates and plays with poses and images from mainstream fashion.

programme.title: Scrum
programme.desc: The lives of a self-assured Canadian jock, a rookie Irish backpacker and a stoic Japanese outsider change when they vie for a position in the grueling Bingham Cup.

programme.title: South Beach On Heels
programme.desc: This award-winning documentary explores the on and offstage lives of eight hard-working drag entertainers. Follow Carmen Carrera, Latrice Royale, and other performers as they search for love, family, and acceptance in an industry built on big hair, big dreams and illusion.

programme.title: No Gender! The Queer Life Of An Intersex Manga Artist
programme.desc: Up until age 30, Sho Arai lived as a woman, but was found to be intersex after chromosome testing.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: S1 E22 | Cardi B and Raven Symoné team up to pull off a lesbian wedding on Facebook's Cardi Tries, before we celebrate Indigenous Peoples’ day by spotlighting two-spirit voices, Canada's Drag Race's Ilona Verley and Being Thunder's Sherenté Harris. Later we look at what a sh*t show Dave Chappelle's Netflix special, The Closer, and North Carolina Lieutenant Governor Mark Robinson's anti-trans rant have created. Finally, we feel inspired by Tom Daley speaking out against homophobia at the 2021 Attitude awards, and Drag Race UK's Charity Kase opening up about what life looks like as an HIV-positive person.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E5 | We interviewed Eden and Stacey at home and at their Synagogue. Eden gave us an informative interview on how ze lives life as a gender non-binary teenager. It was cute to zer ’s mom still struggling with the pronouns, though trying so hard, she respects in every way how Eden identifies and supports zer fully. Stacey and Eden talked to us about being LGBTQ+ in Judaism as well.

programme.title: Gay Camp
programme.desc: A compilation of the films Gay Camp, Justine, The Curse Of The Unkissable Kid, and A Man Doing Man Things

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: Ava's Impossible Things
programme.desc: Ava and her mother Claire are bonded by many things...unconditional love, a passion for the arts, a belief that magic exists, and an insidious disease that will one day end both their lives. It's been three years since Ava moved back into her mother's house to care for Claire, and as Ava witnesses the slow downward spiral all she can do is keep her mother's spirits up while locking away the fears of her own future. Today is a day like any other until rare guests and unexpected events compel Claire to make a shocking announcement, sending Ava into a tailspin. Unable to deal with reality, Ava cries herself to sleep in her mother's arms and escapes to a dream world filled with old friends and long forgotten desires.

programme.title: The Influencers
programme.desc: Six social media influencers compete for an exclusive brand deal with the latest millennial juice craze: Jücytox. As cameras capture each influencer IRL, the manicured versions they present to the world online begin to not just crumble, but implode before our eyes.

programme.title: Gayborhood
programme.desc: S1 E3 | Blaine has big news. Events at a salon opening send ripples through the group. Clay and Leacy throw a party at her Grandma’s.

programme.title: Good Monsters
programme.desc: Eric Stine, a biracial artist, embarks on a cross country journey of discovery, art, and inspiration. Good Monsters is a colorful film that shows Stine’s struggle to understand how his life and work have been affected by his estranged father.

programme.title: Voguing The Message

programme.desc: Step inside the minds of 16 international masters of photography. They share stories behind their most iconic images and techniques whilst learning their impressions of our world as seen through their lenses.

programme.title: I'm From Driftwood
programme.desc: James Clementi Chooses Compassion And Activism After Brother's Death/Man With Cerebral Palsy Recalls First Experience At Gay Bar/Men Are Gay Because They Like Men, You Should Think About Putting On A Little Muscle Next Time/Mom, I’m Gay, Own A Porn Company And Am In A Polyamorous Relationship/Queer, Sexual And Proud, Right Out Of The Womb/Soccer Mom Takes Tomboy To The Gap To Fix Their Gender/The Challenges Of Gender Expression In The Workplace/Transgender Lesbian: I Took A Brave Step To Ensure That I Live In The Light Of Truth/Transgender Man Comes Out To Girlfriend/Transgender Man's Visit To Barbershop Marks New Chapter In Life/Will McGinn: I'm From Staten Island NY - True Gay Stories S1 E21-31 | After the tragic death of his brother Tyler, James decides to live a life of compassion and activism. Andrew, who has Cerebral Palsy and uses a wheelchair, remembers the excitement of going to a gay bar for the first time and the reality that sets in once he arrives. Jason was a ballet dancer during most of his teenage years and into his 20s. He was celebrated for being thin. During one of his first times at a gay bar, he was told he's too skinny and needed to put on some muscle, leading him down a path of taking testosterone and being unhappy. It wasn't until he realized he needed to be happy with who he was because "I wasn’t happy pretending to be someone else." Growing up in a religious household, Benjamine was concerned about having to come out to his mom not only as gay, but as the owner of the successful porn company CockyBoys and being in a polyamorous relationship with two other guys. What he learned from the experience was that “honestly is the best thing in life.” At 5 years old, Noah Michelson did a seductive dance in his underwear for the family's garbage man. After being called "queer", Noah finally had a word to define who he was and how he felt. Renee has always been a tomboy, and now identifies as queer. When Renee was a teen, a neighborhood mom noticed how Renee dressed and took them (Renee uses "they/them/their" pronouns) to The Gap to buy them feminine-looking pants. The experience was traumatic, but also transformational. From wearing Catholic school uniforms in childhood to menswear at a global bank, Erika Miguel has been all over the spectrum of gender expression and fashion. An inappropriate encounter at her job, related to her gender expression, led her to find a new job. Tori Baker went from a rough childhood to drugs to having a daughter and turning her life around. The turning point was realizing that she "can be who I am and like the people that I like.” Mitch was afraid that the relationship might end, but knew it was time to tell his girlfriend that he's transgender. Not only did she support him, they're relationship grew stronger and eventually got married/ Only a few months before a study abroad trip to Rome, Charlie had begun hormone therapy and completed top surgery. He was nervous--about the language barrier and about passing as a male--when he walked into a small barbershop in Rome. Coming out leads to some embarrassing questions from this young man's mom.

programme.desc: In Nazi-occupied Europe, Fredy Hirsch was a proud homosexual Jew. He ran a daycare center for 600 kids in Auschwitz. Fredy was admired by his kids and fought to his last breath to maintain their human dignity.

programme.title: Baby Steps
programme.desc: From Oscar-winning Producer Li-Kong Hsu (Ang Lee’s The Wedding Banquet, Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon, Eat Drink Man Woman) and Stephen Israel (Swimming With Sharks and G.B.F.), comes this multi-cultural comedy-drama, which takes a funny but honest look at gay family issues in complicated dynamo of a cross-generational Taiwanese and American family. Danny, a Taiwanese-American man, longs to have a baby with his American partner Tate, but their attempts at international surrogacy are complicated by Danny’s meddling mother, who wants to control every aspect of the process -- all the way from Taipei.

programme.title: Frameline Voices
programme.desc: A collection of LGBTQ youth-centered shorts with something for audiences of all ages, from the awkward animated memories of Were You Gay in Highschool? to the inspirational story of Zachariah George, aka Mr. Navajo.

Paige, an attorney for Lambda Legal, works on a case representing a trans woman who was denied entry into a women's shelter./Allie and Violet's interview lunch takes a flirtatious turn, and Allie learns that her friend Lisa holds some views that surprise her. A handsome stranger catches Paige's eye./Paige goes out to dinner with James, and it goes a bit differently than her typical dates, while Allie and Violet find they have more in common than they realized.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: MDMA-Assisted Therapy for PTSD

Dr. Mike Hart is back to chat again with us about that report on MDMA-Assisted therapy for severe PTSD. Dr. Hart is the Host of Heart to Hart Podcast and a medical doctor at the Ready To Go Clinic in London, Ontario. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - PTSD very difficult to treat - - Hart says that MDMA-Assisted therapy works because the psychedelic reduces ego - - Hart feels legalization within a year unlikely, and other MDMA-assisted therapy studies will improve

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Dondre Whitfield
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor and author Dondre Whitfield. Dondre Whitfield began his career in a recurring role on the NBC sitcom “The Cosby Show”. programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor Miguel A. Nunez
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor Miguel Nunez. From TV to film, actor Miguel Nunez spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his career, life as a black actor and discuss some of the issues of today.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Ben Crump
programme.desc: DL Hughley Uncut on GFNTV. Guest on DL Uncut is Civil Rights Attorney Benjamin Crump. Attorney Crump is best known for taking on the toughest cases with national civil rights implications. From Trayvon Martin to Michael Brown, Crump continues to push the envelope for justice for those whose lives have been changed due an unfair legal system.

DL, Jasmine and Willy discuss the sport of auto racing, the lack of diversity, and the future of sport in the changing times of America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Lee Merritt
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is attorney Lee Merritt, who is the family attorney for Ahmaud Arbery. Merritt shared the video Tuesday afternoon and said Arbery’s family was forced to watch for the first time online.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Space Channel Exclusive- I4's Dr. Sian Proctor
programme.desc: Dr. Proctor is a geoscientist, explorer, space artist, and astronaut. She is the mission pilot for the Inspiration4 all-civilian orbital mission to space. She is also one of The Explorer’s Club 50: Fifty People Changing the World. Her motto is called Space2inspire where she encourages people to use their unique, one-of-a-kind strengths, and passion to inspire those within their reach and beyond. She believes that we need to actively strive for a J.E.D.I. space: a just, equitable, diverse, and inclusive space as we advance human spaceflight.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Papua New Guinea: The Fire Dance
programme.desc: When a person dies, or to celebrate a harvest or important visit, the Baining tribesmen create masks representing the Spirit of the Forest. A great fire is then lit in the village, and dancers adorning the masks dance around the fire, jumping on the embers to prove they are stronger than the flames.

programme.title: Peru: Masters of Chaos
programme.desc: Anthropologist Anne-Sylvie Malbrancke journeys to meet Jenny, a young Peruvian who has crossed the country to ask the sacred lakes to heal her medical issue. For more than 700 years, shamans have drawn their power to heal from the Huaringas, sacred lagoons located on the border of Peru and Ecuador.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: Wonders of America's National Parks
programme.desc: Travel to lands where monumental forces prevail. Where panoramas of the greatest natural wonders on the planet exist. Products of fire and ice, wind, water, and time, together we will explore the extraordinary wonders of America’s National Parks that elevate the spirit and humble the soul.

programme.title: Mt. Rushmore and the Black Hills
programme.desc: Mount Rushmore stands unrivaled in the world, a sky-high tribute to the heroes and ideals that shaped America. programme.title: Wild National Parks
programme.desc: From grizzly bears of Katmai National Park in Alaska to rattlesnakes of Montezuma's Castle in Arizona, answer the call of America's wildest national parks. By land, sea, and sky, get up close to creatures of all shapes and sizes. Dedicated park workers reveal what it takes to nurture nature.

programme.title: Best of the National Parks
programme.desc: Each year millions from around the world visit America's national parks, lured by images of lands of wonder beyond expression. This exhilarating program reveals the very best locations in America’s national parks to gaze at geysers, spot wildlife, mountain climb, spelunk, and even tie the knot.

programme.title: Yellowstone (1872)
programme.desc: Most of Earth’s geysers are preserved in Yellowstone, including Old Faithful, and they represent the main reason the land became America’s first national park in 1872. Home to mountains and abundant wildlife, Yellowstone is the core of one of the last natural ecosystems in Earth's temperate zone.

programme.title: Yosemite (1890)
programme.desc: First protected in 1864, Yosemite National Park is best known for its waterfalls, but within its nearly 1,200 square miles, you can find deep valleys, grand meadows, ancient giant sequoias, a vast wilderness area, and much more.

programme.title: British Columbia: Vancouver and Beyond
programme.desc: The vibrant city of Vancouver blends the call of the wild with big city charm. Tour historic Gastown and the Capilano Suspension Bridge. Vancouver Island’s capital city, Victoria, defines itself by all things British. Experience ziptrek flights through treetops, and cruise Alaska’s Inside Passage.

programme.title: Canadian Rockies Banff and Jasper
programme.desc: Explore a region famed for its hot springs, backcountry treks, and fantastic array of wildlife, and be treated to elegant dining, and chateaux retreats. Also, enjoy train rides aboard the Rocky Mountaineer, scenic drives along the Continental Divide, and Snocoach rides across treacherous ice fields.

programme.title: Yellowstone: America's First National Park
programme.desc: Vast, beautiful, and untamed, Yellowstone's wilderness ignites the imagination like no other national park. Get a ringside seat for the geothermal wonders, geyser gazing, and diversity of wildlife that gave Yellowstone the nickname, "America's Serengeti."

programme.title: Best Parks to Escape the Crowds
programme.desc: Some of the best national parks attract thousands of spectators every day. If you're looking for a place to go where you won't bump elbows, then take a look at these solitary parks.

programme.title: Christmas in Americas National Parks
programme.desc: It is Christmastime in America’s national parks. Yosemite, Yellowstone, Grand Teton, and Grand Canyon National Parks each offers Christmas visitors their own unique versions of comfort, joy, and the warmth of vintage lodges during the holiday season in the form of festive activities and gatherings.

programme.title: Yosemite America's Treasure
programme.desc: Experience Yosemite's breathtaking icons like the granite monoliths El Capitan and Half Dome and behold the splendor of Bridal Veil and Yosemite Falls. Explore Yosemite's deep history as the first land set aside for preservation, and a land that inspired John Muir and photographer Ansel Adams.

programme.title: Inside Grand Canyon National Park
programme.desc: Experience the supreme and sacred spectacle of the Grand Canyon. This insider’s view of one of the world’s greatest natural wonders takes you rim-to-rim to hike hidden canyons, plunge into ancient pools, raft world-class rapids, discover manmade gems, and explore extreme backcountry.

programme.title: My Hometown Favorites
programme.desc: New York, NY: Passionate about his city, Tony gives us an intimate tour of the New York City foods he loves - sturgeon and bagels, fluke ceviche, pan-seared foie gras, braised veal cheek, authentic cheese and, of course, a hotdog.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: Samoa: Tattoo Heritage
programme.desc: The tattooing practiced in Samoa is not comparable to the fashionable trend in Europe. In Samoa, tattooing is above all a rite signifying that the individual belongs to a group, and it is extremely painful. The more painful it is, the more Stivi approaches the state of a real, accomplished man.

programme.title: Haiti: The Carnival of Specters
programme.desc: Every year in Jacmel, on the southern coast of Haiti, festivities take on an intensity not found elsewhere. Haitians do not depict dream-like characters in their parades, but instead, monsters or specters. This is a way for them to deal with the difficulties of the past, and those of the present.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: Darwin Northern Territory
programme.desc: In Darwin, Jason swims in the Crocodile Tank and visits Litchfield National Park. He also goes heli-pubbing, savours the delicious barra burger, then catches, and cooks, black pepper mud crab. Delicious!

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Yazd, The Zoroastrian Fire Temple
programme.desc: Marvel at the pleasure gardens of Fin in the oasis of Kashan. In the nearby mountains, visit the temple of Chak Chak and become introduced to the ancestral religion of Zoroastrianism. In the sacred city of Yazd, visit a zurkhaneh, or a "house of strength," where athletes engage in training sessions.

programme.title: Bukhara, Light of Transoxiana
programme.desc: Halfway along the ancient Silk Road we arrive in Uzbekistan, first visiting the glorious city of Bukhara, the hometown of Avicenna, and renowned artists and craftsmen. The city’s bazaar is the beating heart of the city, and a bubbling melting-pot of cultures where all manor of items are sold.

programme.title: Samarkand, Pearl Among Cities
programme.desc: Some used to say Samarkand in central Uzbekistan was the center of the world. Follow the ancient "Royal Road" to the city associated with the great Turco-Mongol warrior Timur, visit his mausoleum, and learn about the imposing public square of Registan with the help of a local historian.

programme.title: Fergana, A Central Asian Melting-Pot
programme.desc: The modernity of life in Uzbekistan’s capital of Tashkent is readily apparent, as is the incredible mix of ethnic groups that exist here. Visit a silk factory, a must for anyone retracing the Silk Road, then travel the age-old route through the mountains to Kyrgyzstan, the land of the nomads.

programme.title: How to Be a Carioca
programme.desc: What is a Carioca? The natives of Rio de Janiero, Brazil are lovable scamps who find ways to avoid work, preferring the beach, flirting, and hanging out at restaurants and bars instead. Tony, under the tutelage of an exemplary Carioca, gives the lifestyle a try.

programme.title: Elements of a Great Bar
programme.desc: Join Tony on his quest to characterize the perfect bar in New York City. Discover the importance of a maniacal bartender, the proper chemical makeup of drinks, the joys of seedy dive-bars, and the need for late-night snacks.

programme.title: The Struggle for the Soul of America
programme.desc: Tony travels to the grain-belt capital of Minneapolis, Minnesota to experience firsthand the conflict between creative independent operators and generic franchises.

programme.title: Delhi and Agra, India
programme.desc: From the serene beauty of one man's architectural love poem to a woman, the Taj Mahal, to the crowded alleys of downtown New Delhi, India is a feast for the senses. Maxa discovers temples straight out of Disneyland and consults a street astrologer who tells him he will live a long life.

programme.title: Rajasthan, India
programme.desc: Tour the royal rooms behind the sandstone walls of the Mehrangarh Fort, perched high above the city of Jodhpur. In the countryside outside of Jodhpur, villagers, who have never seen a Westerner, invite Rudy Maxa into their homes, and the maharajah of Jodhpur explains why his palace is now a hotel.

programme.title: Istanbul, Turkey
programme.desc: In Istanbul, evidence of historical invasion exists everywhere. From the Romans to the Ottomans, this tumultuous city has seen it all, and its architecture, cuisine, and customs reflect that reality. Tour the Grand Bazaar, Topkapi Palace, the Hagia Sophia, the Blue Mosque, and the Spice Market.

programme.title: Turkey's Turquoise Coast
programme.desc: Ancient towns of Ephesus, Antalya, Myra and Dalyan dot the Turkish coast, tempting visitors to step back in time when lavish Roman homes and markets dotted the landscape. Boarding a gulet, the traditional wooden Turkish boat, for a Blue Cruise, Rudy departs from the popular seaside town of Bodrum.

programme.title: Bangkok, Thailand
programme.desc: Rudy takes you off the beaten path into the quiet, residential klongs, or canals, of Bangkok. Marvel at the Emerald Buddha, visit the city's fresh markets, join locals offering incense and flowers at colorful outdoor shrines, celebrate the king's 80th birthday with an all-night party, and more.

programme.title: Thailand, The Golden Triangle
programme.desc: The saffron robes of Buddhist monks, the vivid colors of local blossoms, and the brilliant emerald of rice fields make the Golden Triangle a magical corner of the world. Join Rudy as he takes mahout lessons and gets soaked steering his elephant into the river that separates Thailand from Burma.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: France's Via Aquitania
programme.desc: Follow the Via Aquitania, an ancient Roman road that connected a network of cities and was the main trade route between the Mediterranean Sea and the Atlantic Ocean. Traces of the region’s history abound and will become clearer to you the more you hear the people who love this land speak of it.

programme.title: The Volga, Soul of Russia
programme.desc: The Volga River, also called "matuschka,” welcomes world travelers on giant boats. Take a journey of 4,000 kilometers towards the Caspian Sea, from Moscow to Astrakhan, through Laroslav, Nijini Novgorod, Kazan, Samara, and Saratov.

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: How to Be a Carioca
programme.desc: What is a Carioca? The natives of Rio de Janiero, Brazil are lovable scamps who find ways to avoid work, preferring the beach, flirting, and hanging out at restaurants and bars instead. Tony, under the tutelage of an exemplary Carioca, gives the lifestyle a try.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Brazil - A Preserved Beauty
programme.desc: Fernando de Noronha is an archipelago of 21 islands and islets in the Atlantic Ocean. The wild, natural beauty found above and below the sea are the main attractions of the region, where you can observe sea tortoises, dolphins, albatrosses, and some of the most stunning beaches on Earth.

programme.title: Egypt - Water And Sand
programme.desc: Siwa is an island-oasis of fire-torched skies in the middle of the Egyptian desert where The Great Sand Sea comes to rest at the foot of an oasis of date palms. Bordered by two lakes of turquoise blue, travelers find themselves at an oasis that is authentically North African.

programme.title: From Chicago to the Karoo
programme.desc: A healthy mind, body, and environment are all critical for living happy and productive lives. Meet pioneering people in Iraq, Colombia, South Africa, Indonesia, the United States, and Italy who believe in living symbiotically with nature.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Renaissance Europe
programme.desc: Travelers adore Italy, and Italy adores the Renaissance. In this historical half-hour, we follow Western Europe's transitiical sites and museums in favor of a trip--or a day--just for fun.

programme.title: Europe's Getaways
programme.desc: A key attraction of travel on any continent, including Europe, is that 30 minutes outside any city exists a getaway unlike any you will find on the globe. Truly unique locations that resonate with history and significance. Here, we explore a few such places.

programme.title: Montreal, Canada
programme.desc: Join Donna in Montreal and experience the cultural and Epicurean wonders found in this amazing city in Quebec. Also, go jet boating and learn why Montreal is the unofficial "world headquarters" for the circus arts.

programme.title: S8E12 - Berlin
programme.desc: While visiting Berlin's powerful sights — moving memorials, top-tier museums, surviving bits of communist and fascist days — we'll take time to revel in its vibrant social scene.

programme.title: Sydney New South Wales
programme.desc: In Sydney, Jason takes part in some cooking at the award-winning Marque restaurant and meets with an up-and-coming pastry chef at The Blackstar Pastry. For some fun activities, he tries grape stomping and quad biking.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Travel Thru History
programme.desc: In this episode we visit the Kennedy Space Center located on Florida's famous Space Coast. We will speak to NASA engineers about the past, present and future of American space travel, as well as take a look at the attractions K.S.C. has to offer.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: A Taste of Tokyo
programme.desc: Anthony travels to Tokyo, where he begins in the Tsujiki market and then is introduced to techniques in preparing edomae sushi. He also learns the diets of Sumo wrestlers.

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Kyrgyzstan, The Freedom of the Steppes
programme.desc: Osh is first on the list in Kyrgyzstan. Saunter down the aisles of the city’s bazaar and it will soon become clear to you that true Kyrgyzstan is to be found on the steppes and in the mountains. Discover Kyrgyz identity from a student who imparts local legends at the foot of the "Throne of Solomon.”

programme.title: Kashgar, The Gateway to the Middle Kingdom
programme.desc: Kashgar is our point of entry into China. Covering one-sixth of China’s surface area, Kashgar is home to the Uyghurs, an ethnic minority descended from Turkic peoples. When trade on the Silk Road was as its height, Kashgar was a major hub for caravans traveling to India or Central Asia.

programme.title: Bizarre Foods with Andrew Zimmern
programme.desc: From pork shoulder cooked underground to whitefish plucked from Lake Superior, Andrew explores the Upper Peninsula.

programme.desc: Guy heads out on a culinary tour of Maui, Hawaii, with his buddy, chef Reno Henriques; the tour includes loco moco, kalbi ribs, St. Louis-style ribs, burnt ends and a food truck dishing out the freshest catch.

programme.title: Cosmopolitan Comfort
programme.desc: Guy tries all cosmopolitan comfort food. He samples corned beef and cabbage in Portsmouth, New Hampshire, authentic Ethiopian specialties in Los Angeles and over-the-top hot dogs in Minneapolis.

programme.title: Swiss Sandwiches Sausage
programme.desc: Guy stops in Portland, OR, and Charlotte, NC, to sample grilled cheese sandwiches with a twist, made-from-scratch sausages and specialties straight out of Switzerland.

programme.title: Beef Lamb Pig
programme.desc: Guy hunts down all kinds of meaty favorites from cottage pie to Asian-barbeque in Kentucky and North Carolina.

programme.title: Lucky in Love

programme.title: New Mexico True Stories: The Mother Road
programme.desc: A lot of people start out with a casual look at Route 66 and end up making it a life passion.

programme.title: Surf City Women

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.
